summary: This document is an email chain forwarding a request for assistance to Swedish authorities regarding a proposed voluntary interview of an individual in an investigation involving sexual misconduct with a minor. The interview was scheduled for February 5, 2020, and involved coordination with the Swedish National Police.

persons.name: Superintenden
persons.role: Superintendent of the Division of International Affairs/Liaison Unit, Swedish National Police
persons.context: Identified as the point of contact for the Swedish National Police regarding the approval or disapproval of the proposed voluntary interview.

events.title: Proposed Voluntary Interview
events.description: A voluntary interview of an individual was scheduled as part of an investigation involving sexual misconduct with a minor, coordinated with Swedish authorities.

events.title: Request for Assistance Submitted
events.description: A request for assistance was submitted to Sweden concerning the proposed voluntary interview.

keyFacts: The document involves a request for international assistance from Swedish authorities for an investigation into sexual misconduct with a minor.
A voluntary interview of an individual was scheduled for February 5, 2020.
The Swedish National Police, specifically the Division of International Affairs/Liaison Unit, was the point of contact for approving the interview.
The email chain indicates coordination between U.S. and Swedish law enforcement regarding the investigation.
